        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 18 at 12:43PM CST by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 1242 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sherman, or near Athens, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Springfield, Athens, Sherman, Riverton, Mount Pulaski, Williamsville,
Illiopolis, Dawson, Buffalo, Elkhart, Latham, Chestnut, Cornland,
Abraham Lincoln Capital Airport, Illinois State Fairgrounds,
Spaulding, Broadwell, Cantrall, and Fancy Prairie.

This includes Interstate 55 between mile markers 101 and 118.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
